* *********************************************************************************************************************\n**************************************************HOW TO USE *************************************************\n*********************************************************************************************************************\n \nThis model does not include PMBus functionality.  Many parameters set by PMBus are configured by editing the SPICE directives.  \nWhenever possible, the values for the parameters are the same as would be set in the physical hardware.  See below for details and exceptions.  \nHowever, please be aware that:\n-Parameters must be set before a simulation is run.  \n-All parameter values are in decimal format, not hexadecimal or binary format.\n-There is no error checking for parameters that are out-of-range, including non-integer values.  \n-Parameters may be set with a precision that is not realizable in the physical hardware.\n \n********************************************EDITABLE PARAMETERS******************************************\n \n****Control Loop****\n \nValues are the same as in the physical hardware.  Enter each as a decimal integer.\n \nNM_DIGFILT_POLE_SETTING (0xFE03)\nNM_DIGFILT_ZERO_SETTING (0xFE02)\nNM_DIGFILT_HF_GAIN_SETTING (0xFE04)\nNM_DIGFILT_LF_GAIN_SETTING (0xFE01)\n \n****Output Voltage****\n \nValues differ from the physical hardware.  Enter each value directly as a decimal number.  \n \nVOUT_COMMAND (0x21) -- It is not necessary to set VOUT_MODE[4:0]\nVOUT_SCALE_LOOP (0x29)\n \n****Interleaving****\n \nINTERLEAVE (0x37) - only the interleave order is supported (bits [3:0])\n \n****Other Parameters****\n \nValues differ from the physical hardware.  Enter each value directly as a decimal number.  \n \nVIN_ON (0x35)\nVIN_OFF (0x36)\nTON_DELAY (0x60)\nTON_RISE (0x61)\n \n ***************************************************EXAMPLES*****************************************************\n \nExample 1: To set the output voltage to 750mV, enter "VOUT_COMMAND = 750m"\n \nExample 2: To set the scaling of the resistor divider to 0.66, enter "VOUT_SCALE_LOOP = 0.66"\n \nExample 3: To set the interleaving to 90 degrees, set "INTERLEAVE = 4"\n \n **************************************SYNCHRONIZATION FUNCTION****************************************\n \nThe model will automatically synchronize when a 0-3.3V, 50% duty cycle signal is applied to the SYNC pin.  \nEnabling/disabling the SYNC function (register 0xFE55[6]) is not necessary.  \n \n*******************************OTHER FUNCTIONS THAT ARE NOT MODELED ***************************\n \n-Fault handling.\n-Over-current conditions and regulation\n-Startup behavior.  Given the timescales involved, it is also generally impractical and unnecessary to simulate this)
